event,"I've been looking at colleges and preparing for auditions and such! Wow...exciting...but it's gonna get super stressful later T_T Thought I'd announce (to Alyssa, specifically) that the main college I'm looking at is the San Francisco Conservatory of Music! It's the only music conservatory on the west coast and it looks really good. So, Alyssa....if you happen to come across any info about it up there, please let me know! I'm dying to go there. I don't really want to go to SF but a school like that is worth it when there's only two drawbacks: place and price. And in any case, if I'm accepted I'll at least know one person there. event,"Wasted and wounded, it ain't what the moon did

event,"She hangs her head and cries on my shirt.
She must be hurt very badly.
Tell me what's making you sadly?
Open your door, don't hide in the dark.
You're lost in the dark, you can trust me.
'Cause you know that's how it must be.
Her eyes like windows, tricklin' rain
Though my love wants to relieve her.
She walks alone from wall to wall.
Lost in a hall, she can't hear me.
Though I know she likes to be near me.
She sits in a corner by the door.
There must be more I can tell her.
If she really wants me to help her.
I'll do what I can to show her the way.
And maybe one day I will free her.
Though I know no one can see her.
I realized something very shocking last night. It sort of struck some fear into me. The fact that I even housed the ability to feel as I do is a shock. It's scary and it hurts.
I'm being ambiguous. And I like it that way."

column1: event,"I was just out of the service thumbing through the classifieds
When an ad that said:""Old Chevy"" somehow caught my eye
The lady didn't know the year,or even if it ran
But I had that thousand dollars in my hand
It was way back in the corner of this old ramshackle barn
Thirty years of dust and dirt on that green army tarp
When I pulled the cover off,it took away my breath
What she called a Chevy was a sixty six Corvette
I felt a little guilty as I counted out the bills
But what a thrill I got when I sat behind the wheel
I opened up the glove box and that's when I found the note
The date was nineteen-sixty six and this is what it wrote:
He said,""My name is Private Andrew Malone""
If you're reading this,then I didn't make it home""
But for every dream that shattered,another one comes true""
This car was once a dream of mine,now it belongs to you""
And though you may take her and make her your own""
You'll always be riding with Private Malone""
Well it didn't take me long at all,I had her running good
I love to hear those horses thunder underneath her hood
I had her shining lika a diamond and I'd put the rag top down
All the pretty girls would stop and stare as I drove her through town
The buttons on the radio didn't seem to work quite right
But it picked up that oldie show,especially late at night
I'd get the feeling sometimes,if I turned real quick I'd see
A soldier riding shotgun in the seat right next to me
It was a young man named Private Andrew Malone
Who fought for his country and never made it home
But for every dream that's shattered,another one comes true
This car was once a dream of his,back when it was new
He told me to take her and make her my own
And I was proud to be riding with Private Malone
One night it was raining hard,I took the curve too fast
I still dont remember much about that fiery crash
Someone said they thought they saw a soldier pull me out
They didn't get his name, but I know without a doubt
It was a young man named Private Andrew Malone
Who fought for his country and never made it home
But for every dream that's shattered,another one comes true
This car was once a dream of his,back when it was new
I know I wouldn't be here if he hadn't tagged along
That night I was riding with Private Malone
Oh,thank God,I was riding with Private Malone"

Will we all get our chance? The chance that we so greatly deserve? No. But the world isn't even really a Darwinian one anymore (among humans, anyway). Those of us who should succeed, do not, and those who shouldn't, do. There are stupid people running the country, stupid people on our highways...not being victims of accidents...but getting by on luck. Meanwhile...those of us with intellect are constantly put down for the very thing that could save us. But for many, it causes us to give up because we see past the charades. We lack the ability to work with the system because we are so stubborn in our ways. We who have everything that the world wants...We become unwanted because of one single flaw. Would that make us the collective runt? While these successful people harbor less than half the ability both mentally and physically, they win. For those of you who are confused by my ranting...perhaps pair my hard-to-understand explanation with the UCLA admissions. Weird stuff.

The new modern successful person should be able to suck up (whether it be with flattery, manipulation, or seduction), make the best alliances at the perfect time, harbor some great charisma, know a little bit about his/her trade, pretend to be amazing...and the list is endless in that direction of negativity.
The unsuccessful person is often the best for the field that they fail at, and only lack in the fact that one of the aforementioned traits of success is not available to them.

Here's where I tell about my part in this, though many of you might know. I am the unsuccessful. I don't play the game. I could give a shit about what they want from me. I'm in it for my friends, family, and myself. But, really, I'm not in it at all because I don't play the game. I have potential in nearly every aspect of mental, physical, and moral....ness (O_o lol maybe not). I could be anything I want to be with the skills I have. I am interested in nearly everything that I come across. I enjoy knowledge. I enjoy discovery. I enjoy imagination. I enjoy sports. I enjoy psychology. The list goes on. I can be anything. After all, didn't my dad tell me that many 'a' time on his knee?

But, no, I can't. The Game is required reading and I skipped that chapter. They want me to do things that don't benefit me mentally, but only help me to someday (possibly) get to a point where I can benefit myself mentally.

event,"Another late night of rambling and clash of thought.

Family life isn't exactly going great. There isn't an hour that I don't argue with a parent, a stepparent, a sibling...unless I'm secluded within the confines of my room...which I am. I argue with the mothers most. Mom and stepmom. Both of them have opposite views on a lot of things, but somehow...I manage to be against both sides. They're great people...but I think just living with women is not fun. In fact, it often sucks. I rarely see my dad and I'm locked out of his house anyway because my keys were stolen. I'm just at a point where I enjoy being everywhere, except home. The only time I want to be home is either when my dad's home, or when I need/want to be online.

School is pretty good. It's hard and I won't have the best grades for the progress report, but it'll even out as I get used to the homework load. I already am getting better. I'm more organized than I was, not only last year, but in the beginning of this year. My only problem is my lack of sleep. I have had a lot of trouble staying awake in classes. This is also getting better as I get used to being awake 18-20 hours a day.
Band is cool. It has its obvious problems that need fixing, but I think we'll be okay.
Orchestra is absolutely awesome, as is seminar. I swear...I have so many peer families now. It's wonderful.
Love life is lame, as usual. It's practically inevitable.

Homecoming Game is gonna be awesome. We'll probably lose, but everything else will be great. The band will rock and we'll have the gold medalist from the Olympics 400m sprint, who is a graduate of UC, visiting. So basically, publicity MAJOR. If it goes well, we might be able to finally get lights (and TURF!!) for the school stadium. Imagine...last year, nearly 5000 people showed to our Homecoming game. Our team sucked last year too! But people came. I'm thinking, if we had night games, more people would show...which means more money to the school...which means better funds for everything...and more people supporting the school in the community. We have to tap into this community. It's a fairly rich community with a fairly nonrich school...so why not combine them and make the school better. Among all these great things, school spirit will increase a ton! We have none now, but it'll be so much more fun if everyone gets into it. I know that most people can't get into it because other people aren't. Basically, I think the lights are a great investment.

As for the dance, it'll probably be fun. I have tons of friends in several ""families"" who are going happily. Maybe I'll get everyone to take a big picture. That'd be awesome. (lol...awesome is such an awesome word, isn't it? I think it's just awesome. Don't you think it's awesome?) One of my friends asked this girl to HC...I've been teasing him because I never expected him to randomly, after never talking much about girls and stuff, ask someone. But yeah, I told him I know he'd treat me the same if the situation were reversed. In fact, I'd probably be teased more than him =P
Ah well...and that's the way the cookie crumbles. I'm Kaity, signing out."

event,"Confusion is just a thing that sets in. Long lost memories and feelings stirring, while new ones are conjured simultaneously. Lovely. Perfect timing too...Of all things, I don't think I need love during my junior year. It's hard enough. But unfortunately, I can't live without being near people, near someone. What can I say? I guess I'm just a social person. I wish I didn't want it. It just adds to the already chaotic struggle between mind and matter. Self-control. Mind power. My ultimate philosophy fails me. While I'm still controlling my immune system with my mind, other things that I once controlled easily are falling away. I can't concentrate on my school work for very long and things are falling apart. I don't want a repeat of last year and, while I doubt it will repeat, I'm having those same early difficulties...Mind over matter...mind over matter...

I think I might be developing some sort of mental sickness. If not that, at least a physical sickness. I can't breathe very well and I frequently have coughing fits. It's been going on for months now. I've definitely developed a fear of closed spaces and big crowds. I can barely stand being in my room without the window open. My breathing is worse when I'm in those scenarios. I don't know what's wrong with me.
Can't one freaking day go by without the drama?? Damnit...one god damn day."

event,"It's nearly midnight and I'm sort of avoiding my homework while still being very focused on it. Don't ask me how that works, but it's a once in a while thing and I dig it! I wish it happened every time. Umm, so today I went to Wal-Mart and bought me some white boxers because i need them for band because my uniform is white and i have to change in front of everyone. So...there you go. I bought some dickies pants too. They're so awesome. So now I'm just waiting for my laundry to be done before I take a shower and go to bed (all after my homework, of course...-_-) Did I mention it's midnight and my dog is outside barking like hell right outside my window? Ugh.
Edit: damnit...I just yawned and I lost my concentration. *mutters in nerdy voice from Monsters, Inc.* ""You're making me lose my focus!"""

event,"Well, I got a virus. And it won't let me open any programs. Not even Norton Antivirus. Fucking computer. I feel so stpid for falling for the virus' trick too. I was running Norton LiveUpdate....and it asked me to reboot so it could finish the update (LiveUpdate never asks that). So I reboot...when i go to reopen Norton....it won't work. Then I disable the network because i know I have a virus and it would spread to the other computers. Then I go to click on Age of Mythology to ease my mind a bit...it wouldn't open. So I tried every program on my desktop. None of them worked except My Computer and My Documents! So I went to open Add/Remove Hardware....that won't open either. I seriously wanted to kill someone.
